<%# Same MoFU journey scored by Linear vs Participation, side-by-side. %>

<%
  channels = [
    { name: "Blog",     linear: 25, participation: 100 },
    { name: "Webinar",  linear: 25, participation: 100 },
    { name: "Email A",  linear: 25, participation: 100 },
    { name: "Email B",  linear: 25, participation: 80, note: "same channel as Email A &mdash; participation captures it once at full weight" }
  ]
%>

<figure class="my-12 not-prose">
  <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pt-8 pb-6 border-b border-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Linear vs Participation, same journey</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm sm:text-base mt-1">Linear sums to 100% (clean for budget). Participation lets totals exceed 100% on purpose &mdash; that's the signal.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50/60 to-white">

      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-5 gap-y-1.5 mb-5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-slate-600">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-slate-400"></span>
          Linear (sums to 100%)
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-indigo-500"></span>
          Participation (each channel gets full credit)
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <% channels.each do |c| %>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm sm:text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2"><%= c[:name] %></h3>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1.5">
              <div class="w-16 sm:w-24 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-slate-500 shrink-0">LINEAR</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-slate-100 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-slate-400 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= c[:linear] %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-12 sm:w-14 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-slate-700 shrink-0"><%= c[:linear] %>%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-16 sm:w-24 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-indigo-600 shrink-0">PARTICIPATION</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-indigo-50 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-indigo-500 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= c[:participation] %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-12 sm:w-14 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-indigo-700 shrink-0"><%= c[:participation] %>%</div>
            </div>
            <% if c[:note] %>
              <div class="mt-2 pl-19 sm:pl-27 text-xs text-slate-500 italic leading-snug">
                <span class="text-amber-600 font-semibold not-italic mr-1">&#9888;</span>
                <%= c[:note].html_safe %>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>

      <%# Totals row %>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-slate-200">
        <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-md p-3 text-center">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.15em] text-slate-500 mb-1">LINEAR TOTAL</div>
          <div class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-700">100%</div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 italic">budget-ready</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-md p-3 text-center">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.15em] text-indigo-600 mb-1">PARTICIPATION TOTAL</div>
          <div class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-indigo-700">280%</div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-indigo-700 italic">overlap signal</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 py-5 bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-slate-900">When participation totals are much greater than 100%, your channels are working <em>together</em>.</strong>
        That's a feature, not a bug. Cut a channel that scored 100% in participation and you'll affect the deals where it co-occurred with other channels &mdash; not just the deals where it was the only touch.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
  <figcaption class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
    Illustrative MoFU journey &middot; Use Linear for budget allocation, Participation for channel-overlap analysis
  </figcaption>
</figure>
